    "client_msg_id": "d580a0b9-6490-4b1b-8616-8fe226e5ffaf",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Larson claims the limitation with AI is it can only recognize patterns it has seen. Take self driving cars for example. If you're driving behind a pickup truck on the highway and a birthday balloon falls off the back of it, you probably realize it is safe to drive over it. You've never seen this happen before but you know that balloons are filled with air, and its movement suggests it too. What about an AI? Well if it hasn't been trained on this scenario, perhaps it slams on the brakes and causes a collision.",
    "user": "U025PBD75TM",
    "ts": "1633691923.287100",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
